ipxact:field.ipxact:name: PWR_DWN_addr
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Configures behavior of PWR_DWN state. This field is quasi-static. - [7] stuck: if 1'b1, FSM will stop in this state. - [6] bypass: if 1'b1, FSM will bypass this state. Must be mutually exclusive with stuck. - [5] leaving_hibernate: if 1'b1, FSM will run this state when leaving hibernate. - [4:0] next_state: defines the next state. Please check the table for state codes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: DDL_CAL_STATUS0
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Status of Lane 0's DDL calibration - Bit 0 : Signals that the calibration has finished, regardless of the result - Bit 1 : Indicates an error in the calibration (Full bias range was swept with no convergence) - Bit 2 : Indicates an error in the calibration (osc_clk was detected to be stuck) - Bit 3 : Final result is outside of the set acceptable range.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: DDL_CAL_STATUS1
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Status of Lane 1's DDL calibration - Bit 0 : Signals that the calibration has finished, regardless of the result - Bit 1 : Indicates an error in the calibration (Full bias range was swept with no convergence) - Bit 2 : Indicates an error in the calibration (osc_clk was detected to be stuck) - Bit 3 : Final result is outside of the set acceptable range.

ipxact:field.ipxact:description: LP-DCO clock measurement unit trigger override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPCDCOCAL_TWAIT_COARSE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Counter (in cfg_clk cycles) which controls the settling time after changing the coarse setting before performing the next measurement. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPCDCOCAL_TWAIT_PON
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Counter (in cfg_clk cycles) which controls the settling time between enabling the analog circuitry and starting the calibration. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPCDCOCAL_VT_TRACKING_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Enables VT tracking mode where calibration machine will keep monitoring LP-DCO's frequency and adjusting to variations. Active high. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPCDCOCAL_USE_IDEAL_NREF
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Selects which reference target to use in VT tracking mode. This field is quasi-static. - 1'b0: VT tracking mode uses LPCDCOCAL_NREF as reference target. - 1'b1: VT tracking mode uses the result from the power on calibration as reference target.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPCDCOCAL_VT_NREF_RANGE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Defines the tolerance which VT tracking mode still considers to be good. Setting will only be updated if measured LP-DCO frequency deviates from interval [NREF - LPCDCOCAL_VT_NREF_RANGE; NREF + LPCDCOCAL_VT_NREF_RANGE]. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPCDCOCAL_TWAIT_FINE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Counter (in cfg_clk cycles) which controls the settling time after changing the fine setting before performing the next measurement. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LPDCOCAL_N_MEAS
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: dco_clk counter result of last measurement.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_MODE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher mode. This bus is quasi-static. - 4'b0000: pattern matcher disabled - 4'b0001: PRBS31 (x^31 + x^28 + 1) - 4'b0010: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^18 + 1) - 4'b0011: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^21 + x^16 + x^8 + x^5 + x^2 + 1) - 4'b0100: PRBS16 (x^16 + x^5 + x^4 + x^3 + 1) - 4'b0101: PRBS15 (x^15 + x^14 + 1) - 4'b0110: PRBS11 (x^11 + x^9 + 1) - 4'b0111: PRBS9 (x^9 + x^5 + 1) - 4'b1000: PRBS7 (x^7 + x^6 + 1) - 4'b1001: Custom 8 bit pattern - 4'b1010: DC balanced custom 8 bit pattern (pat[7:0], ~pat[7:0]) - all others reserved

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_START_OVR_VAL
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher start override value. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_START_OVR_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher start override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_SAMPLE_COUNTER_OVR_VAL
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher error counter sampling override value. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_SAMPLE_COUNTER_OVR_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher error counter sampling override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_MODE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern generator mode. This bus is quasi-static. - 4'b0000: pattern generator disabled - 4'b0001: PRBS31 (x^31 + x^28 + 1) - 4'b0010: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^18 + 1) - 4'b0011: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^21 + x^16 + x^8 + x^5 + x^2 + 1) - 4'b0100: PRBS16 (x^16 + x^5 + x^4 + x^3 + 1) - 4'b0101: PRBS15 (x^15 + x^14 + 1) - 4'b0110: PRBS11 (x^11 + x^9 + 1) - 4'b0111: PRBS9 (x^9 + x^5 + 1) - 4'b1000: PRBS7 (x^7 + x^6 + 1) - 4'b1001: Custom 8 bit pattern - 4'b1010: DC balanced custom 8 bit pattern (pat[7:0], ~pat[7:0]) - all others reserved

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_START_OVR_VAL
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern generator start override value. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_START_OVR_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern generator start override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_ERROR_INJECTION
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Injects 1 bit error on output pattern. Active high. Each rising edge inserts 1 error.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_DATA_SWAP
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Controls lane mux to choose normal or swapped data (actual reset value is 0xX)

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_USER_PATTERN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Custom 8 bit pattern. Requires LBERT_PG_MODE to be set to 4'b1001 or 4'b1010. This bus is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LP_0_TTAGET_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: BTA timing control. Defines the time that the new transmitter drives LP000 after taking control of the lines. Tta-get timer counter (resolution of 1/2 txclkesc period). This field is quasi-static. Effective timer size is LP_0_TTAGET - LP_0_TTASURE

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LP_0_TTASURE_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: BTA timing control. Defines the time that the new transmitter waits, after the LP10 state before driving LP00. Tta-sure timer counter (resolution of 1/2 txclkesc period). This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LP_0_TTAGO_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: BTA timing control. Defines the time that the transmitter drives LP00 before releasing control of the lines. Tta-go timer counter (resolution of 1/2 txclkesc period). This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LP_0_ITMINRX_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: LP-RX pulse filter width (in dco_clk cycles). Used to reject pulses smaller than the desired size. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LP_1_ERRCONTENTION_THRES_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Error contention detection filter size (in dco_clk cycles). Defines the time that the system tolerates contention before asserting errcontentionlp* flags. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LP_1_LPTX_PON_TIMER_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: LP-TX power on timer (in txclkesc cycles). Defines the time when switching from the ULP pull down back to the LP-TX driver. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_1_FILTER_SIZE_SKEWCAL_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Skew calibration algorithm filter size (word_clk cycles). Corresponds to the number of samples used to assess the quality of a phase setting.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_2_IGNORE_ALTERNCAL_REG

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_2_ROUNDUP_DESKEW_REG

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_TCLKMISS_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Tclkmiss timer counter (dco_clk cycles). Defines the minimum time with absence of clock before flagging clock miss. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_INVORDER_RX_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Signal used to invert MSB to LSB reception order (Active high). This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_INITIAL_CALIBRATION_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Select deskew initial calibration (Active high) If 0 triggers a periodic calibration.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_THSEXIT_MIN_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Controls lane aligner. Used for lower bitrates if bursts received have minimum Ths-exit. This field is quasi-static.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_DESKEW_CNF_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Deskew pattern length configuration for aligner's pattern search. Used for debug purposes. This field is quasi-static. - 2'b00 - Minimum deskew pattern length of 10 bits - 2'b01 - Minimum deskew pattern length of 12 bits - 2'b10 - Minimum deskew pattern length of 14 bits - 2'b11 - Minimum deskew pattern length of 16 bits (default)

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_DESKEW_AUTO_ALGO_SEL_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Select manual or automatic deskew algorithm selection. - 1'b0 - Manual control of the algorithm. HS_RX_7_INITIAL_CALIBRATION_REG selects whether to run an initial calibration or a fine calibration. - 1'b1 - Automatic control of the algorithm. After the first successful initial calibration always run a fine one.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_DESKEW_REARM_INITIAL_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Allows running an initial calibration after a previous successful one when in automatic mode. This feature shall be used in continuous clock mode.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: HS_RX_7_SELECT_ALTERNATE_ALGO_REG
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Selects which algorithm is triggered by the alternate calibration pattern. - 1'b0 - Triggers coarse calibration - 1'b1 - Triggers fine calibration

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_MODE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher mode. This bus is quasi-static. - 4'b0000: pattern matcher disabled - 4'b0001: PRBS31 (x^31 + x^28 + 1) - 4'b0010: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^18 + 1) - 4'b0011: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^21 + x^16 + x^8 + x^5 + x^2 + 1) - 4'b0100: PRBS16 (x^16 + x^5 + x^4 + x^3 + 1) - 4'b0101: PRBS15 (x^15 + x^14 + 1) - 4'b0110: PRBS11 (x^11 + x^9 + 1) - 4'b0111: PRBS9 (x^9 + x^5 + 1) - 4'b1000: PRBS7 (x^7 + x^6 + 1) - 4'b1001: Custom 8 bit pattern - 4'b1010: DC balanced custom 8 bit pattern (pat[7:0], ~pat[7:0]) - all others reserved

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_START_OVR_VAL
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher start override value. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_START_OVR_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher start override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_SAMPLE_COUNTER_OVR_VAL
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher error counter sampling override value. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_SAMPLE_COUNTER_OVR_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern matcher error counter sampling override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_MODE
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern generator mode. This field is quasi-static. - 4'b0000: pattern generator disabled - 4'b0001: PRBS31 (x^31 + x^28 + 1) - 4'b0010: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^18 + 1) - 4'b0011: PRBS23 (x^23 + x^21 + x^16 + x^8 + x^5 + x^2 + 1) - 4'b0100: PRBS16 (x^16 + x^5 + x^4 + x^3 + 1) - 4'b0101: PRBS15 (x^15 + x^14 + 1) - 4'b0110: PRBS11 (x^11 + x^9 + 1) - 4'b0111: PRBS9 (x^9 + x^5 + 1) - 4'b1000: PRBS7 (x^7 + x^6 + 1) - 4'b1001: Custom 8 bit pattern - 4'b1010: DC balanced custom 8 bit pattern (pat[7:0], ~pat[7:0]) - all others reserved

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_START_OVR_VAL
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern generator start override value. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_START_OVR_EN
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Pattern generator start override enable. Active high. Used for debug purposes.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PG_ERROR_INJECTION
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Injects 1 bit error on output pattern. Active high. Each rising edge inserts 1 error.

ipxact:field.ipxact:name: LBERT_PM_DATA_SWAP
ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Controls trio mux to choose normal or swapped data (actual reset value is 0xX)

ipxact:field.ipxact:description: Custom 8 bit pattern. Requires LBERT_PG_MODE to be set to 4'b1001 or 4'b1010. This bus is quasi-static.
